o the four. As\nfor old Maxwell he seemed to have\nd!\\*npearfd r effectually as Bou\nchard and the Madame. 9\nJimmy and his welfare! What to\ndo w. h Jimmy. That was the sub\nj on an\u201d and all occasions when i\nthe four rwt. Three specialists had\nexamined him. Each one prescribed j\na treatment that was different in I\neveral n peels, but on one point1\nthey all agreed. Jimmy should be j\na' wed, they declared, another six\n11.tbs I. which lo sh\u00bbw it tat na\nture would do. And all prescribed\na sea voyage in tropical waters.\nIt was \"larks, the lawyer, who\nprovided the su-ge tion regarding\nthe l' t means for a sea voyage,\nbe.: for Jimmy and one In which\nhis friends bright nartirinate.\n\"I b :lv har his or her troub\nle i.\" hr remarked during the course\ncf a c'n.\u2019rrr'J: i one evening a\u2018\nthe Lynn? home. \u201cThere\u2019s en old\nfriend\u2014and client\u2014of mine. How\nard Wmk'v. H 'r, worth p couple\nof m lions is In good henlth er.1\nnot yet foriy. And with all that\nWhn am I? 11 h ,t city am I a\njr For v... hi.:d of cases am I\nnoted?\nTf..r* many women came to Vir\nginia with the firrt settlers in 1607?\nWhat Is the symbol of Tammany\nHail?\nYc Judge after the flesh; I Judge\nno man.\u201d Where is this passage\nlour.d In the Bible?\nCorrect\u2019y Speaking\nWhen y u arc not feeling well say.\n*1 am ill,\u201d not \"I am poorly.\"\nToday\u2019s Anniversary\nOn t ry, in 1703. Thomas Mal\nthus. tii> English political economist,\nwas born.\nToday's Horoscope\nPersons born cn this clay are very\nartistic and make large profits\nthrough this trait.\nAnswers to Forgoing Questions\n1. Joseph Sabath; Chicago; di\nvorce.\n2. None.\n3. Tiger.\n4. St. John. Till, 13.\nStar Lore\n\u201cA S\"LF-MOVE!t\"\nEy Arthur DeV. Carpenter\nWe r e in rec'ipt cf a letter from\na perpcaral m: on, \"a self-mover\u201d:\nc: al me u a sa f-m :ver**;\nren It. hi tan\ntk he in mfc to p i h.s\nhrt v rto know h'w ho\n7 let to -.ite his haven\nI re a p r f i\ni is will rv dit him and pro\n-t h.o rights. The recdw will ray\nV.-/ e c* have the sound cf a\nself-dr sieved r:an. Eleven years ago\nthe writer me; a man in California\nwho h id invented a perpetual mo\ntion, explained the principle and\nsaid: in about two weeks you will\nI hr; .11 about it, as it will be writ\nten up in the papers.\u201d\n1 ^Continued Tomorrow)\nlife for him tonight seems hardly\nworth the living.\n\"Howard was married five years\nago,\" went on Marks. \u201cHe married\nthe girl of his boyhood dreams.\nTheir married life has been ideal.\nA few months ago he bought a\nsplendid power yacht. Gave two\nhundred thousand dollars for it.\nThe craft is two hundred feet from\nstem to gudgeon. It has fourteen\nprivate staterooms in addition to\nthe crew\u2019s quarters. It carries a\ncrew of twenty, comprising the\ncaptain, two mates, wireless oper\nators. steward, chef and second\ncook; two waiters, two cabin boys,\ntwo engineers, two oilers\u2014she burns\noil\u2014and five deck hands. The cap\ntain\u2019s and first mate\u2019s cabins are\non the top deck and adjoining the\npilot house.\n\"My client and his wife with a\nparty of six friends, had planned\nto leave New York this week for\na trip around the world. Last Sat\nurday she and he were out riding\nin his car. He was driving. They\nwere speeding along Madison ave\nnue wl*^i he lost control for an\ninstant and smashed into a big\ni truck. His wife was hurled through\nthe windshield. She died in five\nminute*. He was unhurt\u2014physical\nly. Mentally Howard Wlckly is\nclose to being a madman. Just to\n1 mention the yacht in his heading\nalmost drives him wild. One could\nbuy the craft mighty cheap. I\nreckon!\"\nAs the statement aroppea irom uu\nUps Pat straightened up In her\n'\u2022hair, h*r eyes suddenly aglow as\nthe new idea struck her.\n-Why wouldn't that be Just the\nthing for Jimmy?\" she queried as\nif she were considering the purchase\nof a new toy for him to play with.\nShe glanced around the little group\ninquiringly. \u201cA cruise of five or six\nI months through tropical waters\u2014\nthat'5 what the doctors ta.d!\" She\nturned to the lawyer. \u201cDo you aup\npose. Mr. Marks?\" she a kcd. \u201cthat\nI could buy the yacht fer what he\nj paid for it?\u201d\n\u201cI'm sure you could,\" replied the\nlawyer, who knew she could buy it\nfor much less. \u201cAnd it would, as you\ni say. be just the thing for Jimmy!\nIf \"you want me to I\u2019ll call him up J\nI In the morning and get a price on\nit!\"\nThe idea met with the Instant ap\nproval of not only Rex, Frank and\nMargery, but of Aunt Lottie as well, i\nShe always had been crazy to go j\naway cn a long yachting trip, she\ndeclared.\nMarks telephoned Pr.t shortly aftc*\nnoon the following dry, informing\nher that Wiokly's yacht, the Blue\ni d. could he purchased fer $180,\nOOd cash. It was insured, he had\nh r:*cd, for that amount with the\npremiums paid up for six months\nPat gave the lav;, :r instructions to\nnegotiate the purchase at cnee with\nthe provision that she and her\nfriends should first inspect It. He\nhad already arranged for that, he\ntw.d her. Fat u*..ncd*:uc.y caii\ncd Daliard and the doctor\nand acquainted ;.hr:n with the law\nyers report. As a result Margery\nand she. w*th Aunt Lottie and Jim\nmy met the men at their p'.tcc\nnear Gramercy Park where Marks\nJoined them, and the party was\ntiiiven to a dock near the foot ol\nFifty-first street and the Hudson\nwhere the Bluebird was moored.\nCaptain Seth Lee and the first\nmate, Carl Johnson, the first engi\nneer. John Lake, the steward. Prt\u00b0r\nBronson and the chef. Antoine Ve\nlasse. were aboard at the lime o:\nthe visit. They all expresied them\nselves as pleased at the prospect of\nan early cruise. The yacht s regular\ncrew, the captain said, was still\nwith them with the exception of\nthree deck hands who would have tc\nbe engaged.\nThe new owner-to-be and her\nfriends were escorted over and\nthrough tha craft by Captain Lee\nand Mr. Johnson, first officer. The\nBluebird was found to be a splend\nidly built and equipped yacht. Slime\nfrom davits on the starboard sidr\n(DRY) LAND AT LAST?\nI .transfer tc/X\nt^jHE DEPToFOUST(Ce|\n\nhigh up so as to permit one to walk\nunderneath along the passage be\ntween cabin and rail was a late\nmodel motor boat thirty feet long\nand with a carrying capacity of\nthirty persons. On the port side\nwere two small boats, ordinary row\ning boats.\nThere were fourteen perfectly ap\npointed staterooms, each with two\ndouble berths, upper and lower, a\ntiny toilet and shower bath, three\neasy chairs and a chiffonier. These\nsalerooms were provided with\ndouble-paned and screened windows\nlooking across the passageway be\ntween rail and cabin. j\nThe main cabin, which also served\nas a dining cabin, was seventy feet\nlong and luxuriously furnished. Re\nmoval of the big rug permitted danc\n\nATTENTION! j\nWe have added a\nRental Library to our\nstore! Come in and look I\nit over. All of the best\nsellers of all publishers.\nKeep abreast of the\nmost popular new books\nby renting them at\nsmall cost!\nj HARGROVE\u2019S\nI Stationery Book Store\nPhone 348\nBrownsville, Texas\nINeed less\nPain?\n\nSome folks take pain for granted.\nThey let a cold \u201crun its courts.\u2019!\nThey wait for their headaches to \u201cwear off.'l\nIf suffering from neuralgia or from neuritis*\nthey rely on feeling better in the morning.\nMeantime, they suffer unnecessary pain.\nUnnecessary, because there is an antidote.\nBayer Aspirin always offers Immediate relief\nfrom various aches and pains we once had to\nendure. If pain persists, consult your doctor\nas to its cause.\nSave yourself a lot of pain and discomfort\nthrough the many uses of Bayer Aspirin. Pro\ntect yourself by buying the genuine. Bayer ia\nsafe. Always the same. All drugstores.\nBAYER ASPIRIN\n)Aepiria ia lea trade mark of Bayer Manufacture of Monoaeeticacidaatar of SalicyUcadd\ning on a floor built like the runway1\nof a bowling alley. The engine room\nwas. of course, below decks, the up\nper part Inclosed with a four-foot\npassageway on each sid*. Forward\nof the galley was the crew s quar\nters. Taken In Its entirety the yacht\nwas the ideal pleasure craft for a\nparty of ten to twenty persons on a\nround-the-world voyage.\nPat\u2019s party, it was noted, would\nnumber nine, namely: Margery.\nAunt Lottie, Lucy Pine and herself\nwith Jimmy. Rex Dallard. Dr. Gor\ndon and the lawyer, Marks, and his 1\nwife. The girls and Aunt Lottie\nhad already met Mrs. Marks on\ntwo or three occasions.\nTO BE CONTINUED*\nEat At\nAnthony\u2019s Waffle\nShop\n517 12 St Phone 983\nA. TAMM\nBlue Printing and\nSupplies\nHarlingen, Texas\n1911 1930\nSkelton Abstract Co.\nAbstracts of Title Title Insurance\nMerchants Bank Building Brownsville\n________________________\nDependable Phone 353 Prompt\nBROWNSVILLE TITLE COMPANY\nBROWNSVILLE, TEXAS\nAbstracts of Title Title Insurance\nWe cover all lands In Cameron County\nCARNEIRO, CHUMNEY COMPANY\nCertified Public Accountants\nIncome Ta* Serrlce\nBROWT8VILLE SAN ANTONIO CORPU8 OHRI8TI\nState National Ban!: Smith-Young Twer Nixon Building\n[^PROSPERITY\nProsperity for Brownsville and\nthe Valley is a tangible, able-to\nbe-seen condition. Citrus groves\nare beginning to bloom vege\ntables are commanding good\nprices generally the interna\ntional airport and the bright\nprospects for a deep water port\u2014\nall are encouraging a splendid\nbusiness outlook for Brownsville\nand the Valley.\nLet us. as your bank, help\nyou with any problems you\nmay wish to discuss with us.\nFirst National Bank\nEstablished in 1891\nBROWNSVILLE, TEXAS\nTITLE INSURANCE J\nWhen yon borrow money on real estate, many loan rom;Mniet re-\nquire the title to be Insured. In* best test of whether a title te\ninsurable, la to have it insured. Require a title insurance policy\nwhen you buy.\nI VALLEY ABSTRACT COMPANY\nPrompt Title Service\nBrownsville\nOpposite Court House\nPhone 1184\